1
00:00:06,457 --> 00:00:09,719
<i>There's an old story of a
father who had two sons.</i>

2
00:00:09,743 --> 00:00:12,356
<i>When he knew a civil
war was about to break out,</i>

3
00:00:12,380 --> 00:00:16,030
<i>he sent one son to fight for
the North, and one to the South.</i>

4
00:00:18,385 --> 00:00:21,080
<i>He figured if he had
sons on both sides,</i>

5
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:23,338
<i>there'd be a better
chance one would survive.</i>

6
00:00:35,769 --> 00:00:39,855
<i>Because when you fight a war at
home, the casualties are your neighbors...</i>

7
00:00:47,581 --> 00:00:49,314
<i>your friends, your family.</i>

8
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:57,021
<i>Leaving you all alone.</i>

9
00:01:06,366 --> 00:01:08,061
I need you to do something.

10
00:01:09,185 --> 00:01:12,899
I told you I'd do it. Just
separate out the delicates.

11
00:01:12,923 --> 00:01:15,090
Not laundry. My thing is fun.

12
00:01:15,676 --> 00:01:17,887
I need you to clip an
aneurysm at the hospital.

13
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:20,951
- I'm on leave. Yeah, I
need you to be off leave.

14
00:01:21,749 --> 00:01:23,509
- No.
- Please. Come on,

15
00:01:23,533 --> 00:01:26,329
it's a sweet little old nun and
she needs open heart surgery,

16
00:01:26,353 --> 00:01:29,031
but she can't have it until
her brain aneurysm is clipped.

17
00:01:29,055 --> 00:01:30,335
It's so sad.

18
00:01:31,075 --> 00:01:33,769
- Poor Sister Agnes.
- Don't "nun" me.

19
00:01:33,793 --> 00:01:36,172
The nun detail was a
little bit much. But please.

20
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:38,442
Please, come on. I
need you. You're the best.

21
00:01:38,466 --> 00:01:40,965
And don't tell me that
you don't miss the O.R.

22
00:01:41,852 --> 00:01:45,492
Just one little clip, and you
can scratch that itch. Just...

23
00:01:45,606 --> 00:01:48,139
One little clip.
You'll be in and out.

24
00:01:48,625 --> 00:01:52,144
And I'll make sure that Owen
doesn't see you. I promise.

25
00:01:55,565 --> 00:01:57,315
Give me ten minutes.

26
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,248
Morning. Good to have you back.

27
00:02:02,272 --> 00:02:04,717
- Morning. Thank you.
- So, um, when I was chief...

28
00:02:04,741 --> 00:02:05,741
Interim chief.

29
00:02:07,077 --> 00:02:09,005
I took the liberty
of catching you up

30
00:02:09,029 --> 00:02:10,523
on all your backlogged
resident reports,

31
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:12,859
department budgets,
supply orders, so...

32
00:02:12,883 --> 00:02:14,377
- I was gonna do that.
- Of course, you were.

33
00:02:14,401 --> 00:02:17,179
I just figured, you know, same
way you fill the tank with gas

34
00:02:17,203 --> 00:02:19,654
- when you return someone's car.
- You stole the car.

35
00:02:21,926 --> 00:02:23,241
You're welcome.

36
00:02:24,377 --> 00:02:26,027
Ah. Look who's back.

37
00:02:27,297 --> 00:02:29,576
Have to say, I thought
you'd last longer.

38
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,394
- You folded quick.
- I didn't fold.

39
00:02:31,418 --> 00:02:34,146
You're here, aren't you? And
the chief didn't fire Minnick.

40
00:02:34,170 --> 00:02:36,499
Dr. Webber asked me to come
back. There was no folding.

41
00:02:36,523 --> 00:02:37,803
If you say so.

42
00:02:42,679 --> 00:02:44,724
If you're into the guy,
why not just be with him?

43
00:02:44,748 --> 00:02:46,760
- Because I don't want to
be with him. Oh, come on.

44
00:02:46,784 --> 00:02:48,645
Is it because of
Maggie? She'll get over it.

45
00:02:48,669 --> 00:02:51,464
- No, I don't wanna be with him.
- Okay. You do, though.

46
00:02:52,973 --> 00:02:54,172
But I don't.

47
00:02:56,293 --> 00:02:59,613
<i>Pain Management to the ICU.
Pain Management to the ICU.</i>

48
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:06,951
- So, listen, are we cool?
- What do you mean,
"Are we cool?"

49
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:10,166
I don't want there to be
any problems with patients.

50
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,334
It's just...

51
00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:13,620
are we cool, I mean,
to work together?

52
00:03:13,644 --> 00:03:17,290
- We're cool.
- I had to ask. It's kids.

53
00:03:17,314 --> 00:03:19,859
- We're cool.
- Okay. Good.

54
00:03:19,883 --> 00:03:24,119
<i>Dr. Jacoby, 1011.
Dr. Jacoby, 1011.</i>

55
00:03:24,738 --> 00:03:26,215
- The mattresses?
- Yes.

56
00:03:26,239 --> 00:03:29,535
You need to replace every mattress
in every on-call room. Unacceptable.

57
00:03:29,559 --> 00:03:31,103
He's not wrong.

58
00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:34,957
These mattresses are lumpy, they're
misshapen, zero lumbar support.

59
00:03:34,981 --> 00:03:36,759
Our surgeons need solid rest,

60
00:03:36,783 --> 00:03:39,028
- not spinal damage.
- Noted.

61
00:03:39,052 --> 00:03:41,981
You might tell Dr. Webber
that if he wants to sleep soundly,

62
00:03:42,005 --> 00:03:45,101
he should come home
and sleep next to his bride.

63
00:03:46,777 --> 00:03:50,006
I'll take this under advisement.

64
00:03:52,099 --> 00:03:55,411
- New mattresses!
- Hey. You okay?

65
00:03:55,435 --> 00:03:57,152
No. My back hurts.

66
00:03:57,521 --> 00:03:59,833
Oh, and there's nothing like
having your dirty laundry aired

67
00:03:59,857 --> 00:04:01,901
- for everyone to see.
- Hm, it's that bad, huh?

68
00:04:01,925 --> 00:04:04,343
Yeah, as long as Minnick's
here, it's gonna stay bad.

69
00:04:05,412 --> 00:04:10,142
I-I don't know what to do,
except maybe give up and give in.

70
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:12,562
No. No, that's not acceptable.
Everyone's behind you.

71
00:04:12,586 --> 00:04:14,119
Everyone was behind me.

72
00:04:14,772 --> 00:04:16,565
The longer Minnick's here,
the more people like her.

73
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:17,767
And the more people like her...

74
00:04:17,791 --> 00:04:20,236
Well, I'm behind you,
then, so... Hey, listen.

75
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,155
Why don't you stay at my
place? I have a guest room,

76
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:25,129
- and it's got
a very good mattress.
- I-It'll be fine.

77
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:30,802
Arizona, thanks for sticking
with me. You're a good friend.

78
00:04:38,595 --> 00:04:40,573
We're losing ground.
Everybody loves Minnick.

79
00:04:40,597 --> 00:04:42,425
I wouldn't say that. I
mean, who said that?

80
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:44,928
- And now Meredith.
- I stood up for him
and got suspended.

81
00:04:44,952 --> 00:04:46,345
Yeah, and now you're
back. You rolled over.

82
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:49,315
- Because he told me
to come back!
- That's not what it looks like!

83
00:04:49,339 --> 00:04:50,716
All right, you weakened
our position here.

84
00:04:50,740 --> 00:04:54,187
Well, we don't have a position
if he is asking us to stop.

85
00:04:54,211 --> 00:04:56,139
- Meredith has a point.
- The problem isn't Minnick.

86
00:04:56,163 --> 00:04:57,623
The problem is that
her program is good.

87
00:04:57,647 --> 00:04:59,526
And now everyone
knows it, including Richard.

88
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:01,311
You guys are unbelievable.
You're just gonna abandon him now?

89
00:05:01,335 --> 00:05:02,578
- No, we're not.
- No.

90
00:05:02,602 --> 00:05:04,531
Well, I'm not gonna do
that. I'm gonna fight for him.

91
00:05:04,555 --> 00:05:05,998
- How?
- My mother's not the only Avery

92
00:05:06,022 --> 00:05:07,272
in this hospital.

93
00:05:11,762 --> 00:05:15,708
Seems like the colovesical
fistula closed off on its own after all.

94
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:18,250
No abdominal
reconstruction needed.

95
00:05:18,619 --> 00:05:21,814
Good. I was hoping to avoid
having to call Jackson in.

96
00:05:21,838 --> 00:05:23,466
Things still difficult at home?

97
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:25,551
I'm not sure I can
stay there anymore.

98
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:26,602
I mean, I want to.

99
00:05:26,626 --> 00:05:29,622
It's been so easy
with Harriet, but...

100
00:05:29,646 --> 00:05:32,592
But everything's so much harder
than it needs to be right now.

101
00:05:32,616 --> 00:05:34,978
- I know.
- Yeah. And...

102
00:05:35,002 --> 00:05:36,602
And what?

103
00:05:37,871 --> 00:05:41,601
It's just embarrassing,
being demoted.

104
00:05:41,625 --> 00:05:42,874
You were not demoted.

105
00:05:43,110 --> 00:05:45,254
From chief of general surgery to
trauma attending? It looks like it.

106
00:05:45,278 --> 00:05:49,230
April. April. A title is only as
good as the person who earned it.

107
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:52,811
Grey is very good, but
when she wasn't here,

108
00:05:52,835 --> 00:05:55,153
the person they
turned to was you.

109
00:05:55,472 --> 00:05:57,512
- Oh, I know...
- Do you?

110
00:05:57,573 --> 00:05:58,951
Then act like it.

111
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:09,117
So, hey. Heads, he's Leo.

112
00:06:10,086 --> 00:06:11,781
Let's just wait until
we know he's okay.

113
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:14,889
Oh, come on, stop. You agreed
that we'd decide with a coin toss.

114
00:06:15,642 --> 00:06:17,570
I noticed a systolic murmur
at the post-birth exam.

115
00:06:17,594 --> 00:06:19,338
It's probably nothing,
but I called just in case.

116
00:06:19,362 --> 00:06:21,913
I'll check it out.
DeLuca, get a pulse ox.

117
00:06:24,234 --> 00:06:26,651
Baby, our little guy is
gonna need a name.

118
00:06:27,304 --> 00:06:29,532
Hey, definitely before school,
but probably before we leave here.

119
00:06:29,556 --> 00:06:31,216
So...

120
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:33,925
Heads, he's Leo. Tails, August.

121
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:38,763
- Okay, why is the name
I like tails?
- Fine. Heads, he's August.

122
00:06:43,269 --> 00:06:47,155
- Heads?
- August it is.

123
00:06:47,841 --> 00:06:49,602
Pulse ox is slightly
below normal.

124
00:06:49,626 --> 00:06:52,344
Yeah. Let's get some
labs and page Cardio.

125
00:06:54,364 --> 00:06:55,674
Uh, what's
happening? Is he okay?

126
00:06:55,698 --> 00:06:58,778
He's got a heart murmur. I need
to take him to get some tests.

127
00:06:58,802 --> 00:07:01,122
I'll let you know
more as soon as I do.

128
00:07:01,154 --> 00:07:02,874
- What's the little guy's name?
- Gus.

129
00:07:03,156 --> 00:07:04,189
Gus.

130
00:07:13,650 --> 00:07:14,966
Hey. You got a minute?

131
00:07:15,301 --> 00:07:17,196
Uh, just got paged
to the pit. Can it wait?

132
00:07:17,220 --> 00:07:18,614
- Thanks.
- I need to talk to you

133
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:20,733
- about this Minnick situation.
- What situation? She's doing great.

134
00:07:20,757 --> 00:07:22,535
Don't pretend you don't
know what you did, Mom.

135
00:07:22,559 --> 00:07:24,587
People have been fighting this
since the minute you brought her here.

136
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:26,756
- Bailey brought her here.
- At your urging.

137
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:28,708
And since I am the voice of
the Avery Foundation at this...

138
00:07:28,732 --> 00:07:30,643
Wait. I'm sorry.
You're the what?

139
00:07:30,667 --> 00:07:33,429
I'm the foundation's
representative on the board, right?

140
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:35,614
A position that you gave
me, that you made me take.

141
00:07:35,638 --> 00:07:38,817
Yes, and you kicked and screamed
and whined every step of the way.

142
00:07:38,841 --> 00:07:40,475
And then I took it on.

143
00:07:41,578 --> 00:07:44,757
So I am the Avery of this hospital.
The foundation speaks through me.

144
00:07:44,781 --> 00:07:47,293
The foundation
oversees, we guide.

145
00:07:47,317 --> 00:07:48,761
We do not interfere
in hospital politics.

146
00:07:48,785 --> 00:07:50,668
How can you say that to me?

147
00:07:51,154 --> 00:07:53,883
You started this by effectively
ousting Richard Webber.

148
00:07:53,907 --> 00:07:56,590
Which, by the way, our rank and
file finds completely unacceptable.

149
00:07:58,028 --> 00:08:00,323
I'm gonna be making
the decisions from now on.

150
00:08:00,347 --> 00:08:01,624
I'm gonna go to
the governing board,

151
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:03,531
I'm gonna get Richard
back in and Minnick out.

152
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:05,216
I'm going over your head.

153
00:08:22,536 --> 00:08:25,415
I don't understand. He's never
been that interested in the foundation.

154
00:08:25,439 --> 00:08:29,268
I know. He does not appreciate
our role, or the scope of it.

155
00:08:29,292 --> 00:08:33,606
Seventy-seven hospitals nationwide,
forty-three full service clinics.

156
00:08:33,630 --> 00:08:35,725
Not to mention the
Worldwide Health Initiative.

157
00:08:35,749 --> 00:08:38,761
Oh, somebody's been
doing her homework.

158
00:08:38,785 --> 00:08:40,196
I've just been curious.

159
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:42,687
Or maybe you just
like being in charge.

160
00:08:43,206 --> 00:08:44,868
You know, the thing is...

161
00:08:44,892 --> 00:08:46,986
- I was good at that job.
- Mm-hmm.

162
00:08:47,010 --> 00:08:50,656
I like doing that stuff, the
admin work, the scheduling.

163
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:51,941
Meredith doesn't even like it.

164
00:08:51,965 --> 00:08:55,516
You know, I want you to see the
Avery Trauma Center in Chicago.

165
00:08:55,852 --> 00:08:57,830
They do things very
differently than you do here.

166
00:08:57,854 --> 00:08:59,332
- We should go.
- Absolutely.

167
00:08:59,356 --> 00:09:00,716
I would love to see
how they run things.

168
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:02,974
No, honey. I want them
to see how you run things.

169
00:09:03,493 --> 00:09:06,071
Oh, yeah. I'd love
that. Thank you.

170
00:09:06,095 --> 00:09:07,335
Trauma One.

171
00:09:08,348 --> 00:09:10,109
- What have we got?
- Turkey fryer accident.

172
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:12,311
Propane tank exploded.
Blew shrapnel everywhere.

173
00:09:12,335 --> 00:09:15,031
His family's behind him, minor injuries,
but he caught got the brunt of it.

174
00:09:15,055 --> 00:09:17,633
Full-thickness burns to the neck,
down the left side of his body,

175
00:09:17,657 --> 00:09:19,101
extending into the perineum.

176
00:09:19,125 --> 00:09:22,377
- Left leg partially degloved.
- One, two, three.

177
00:09:25,181 --> 00:09:27,181
Suture kit and trauma dressing.

178
00:09:28,034 --> 00:09:29,928
All right, check on that gauze.

179
00:09:29,952 --> 00:09:31,647
Oh, wow.

180
00:09:31,671 --> 00:09:33,149
His bowel is eviscerated.

181
00:09:33,173 --> 00:09:35,551
I need to examine this
wound and the perineal burn.

182
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,935
- Somebody call Plastics!
- On it.

183
00:09:39,328 --> 00:09:42,864
Yeah. So this kid
definitely has HLHS.

184
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:45,378
- Start him on PGE.
- Labs are back.

185
00:09:45,402 --> 00:09:48,497
All righty, Gus. Let's
take a look at your labs.

186
00:09:48,521 --> 00:09:51,283
- They landed on Gus, huh?
- How did their OB
not catch this?

187
00:09:51,307 --> 00:09:53,636
Okay, DeLuca, we need to get
him on the transplant list ASAP.

188
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:57,729
Hold on. No, we're
gonna do a Norwood.

189
00:09:58,197 --> 00:10:00,309
Well, I don't think so. He
has mitral valve regurg.

190
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:03,112
I don't think the little kid can
survive a full reconstruction like that.

191
00:10:03,136 --> 00:10:05,456
I know he won't survive the
wait for a newborn donor heart.

192
00:10:05,622 --> 00:10:07,822
He's stable for now. He
can tolerate a Norwood.

193
00:10:08,641 --> 00:10:10,569
- So, what's next?
- Parents are freaking out.

194
00:10:10,593 --> 00:10:11,976
We go talk to them next.

195
00:10:18,885 --> 00:10:20,930
- Where did they take Dad?
- Let me check you out.

196
00:10:20,954 --> 00:10:22,448
It's okay, Pammy.
It's gonna be okay.

197
00:10:22,472 --> 00:10:25,718
Your fiancé just deep fried
our father! That is not okay!

198
00:10:25,742 --> 00:10:27,470
- This is from a turkey fryer?
- It's the one thing

199
00:10:27,494 --> 00:10:30,172
I know how to cook. I was just
trying to do something special.

200
00:10:30,196 --> 00:10:33,042
You mean unforgettable? Like
"that time you killed my dad"?

201
00:10:33,066 --> 00:10:36,479
- Pam! Come on! He didn't mean to!
- Rodney, Dad's leg melted off!

202
00:10:36,503 --> 00:10:39,482
- You have no eyebrows!
- I'm so sorry, honey. So sorry.

203
00:10:39,506 --> 00:10:41,317
- I know.
- Your arm has
a partial thickness burn.

204
00:10:41,341 --> 00:10:42,851
You'll need to learn to
dress it while it heals.

205
00:10:42,875 --> 00:10:44,575
I can help. How can I help?

206
00:10:44,994 --> 00:10:47,273
Oh, I don't know, go back
in time when I told you,

207
00:10:47,297 --> 00:10:49,257
"Deep fryers are
dumb" and listen to me!

208
00:10:50,183 --> 00:10:51,577
Can you tell me
how my father is?

209
00:10:51,601 --> 00:10:54,819
- Pam, I'm sorry.
- Maybe just stop talking.

210
00:10:55,689 --> 00:10:58,849
Someone will come dress those
burns. And I'll go get an update.

211
00:11:02,979 --> 00:11:04,540
All right, he's got a
lot of neck swelling.

212
00:11:04,564 --> 00:11:06,792
Um, can you get me a
fiberoptic scope, just in case?

213
00:11:06,816 --> 00:11:08,777
This wound extends deep.
The bladder is destroyed.

214
00:11:08,801 --> 00:11:10,980
I need to get him in
an O.R. for a repair.

215
00:11:11,004 --> 00:11:12,581
No, you can do the
bladder repair later.

216
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:15,167
I need to do an ex-lap with
an abdominal washout first.

217
00:11:15,191 --> 00:11:16,702
Yeah, I can't even
see his vocal cords.

218
00:11:16,726 --> 00:11:18,604
- Here. Let me try.
- No, I got it. I got it.

219
00:11:18,628 --> 00:11:21,074
Okay. Warren, call up to the
O.R., tell them to place the patient

220
00:11:21,098 --> 00:11:23,876
in lithotomy position
for a perineal evaluation.

221
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:25,978
Warren, let them know we
need a perc nephrostomy setup

222
00:11:26,002 --> 00:11:28,080
and a possible ileal
conduit for reconstruction.

223
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:29,865
His small bowel is
sticking out of his abdomen.

224
00:11:29,889 --> 00:11:31,217
What ileal conduit
are you talking about?

225
00:11:31,241 --> 00:11:33,936
Jackson, the tendon is exposed.
He's gonna need a skin flap.

226
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:36,105
- No, no, that can wait.
- I'm just saying...

227
