I'm sorry. Sorry.

689
00:38:52,531 --> 00:38:53,963
<i>War isn't civil.</i>

690
00:38:55,233 --> 00:38:58,251
<i>You pick sides and
defend them. You attack.</i>

691
00:39:07,228 --> 00:39:09,629
<i>You hurt people. You get hurt.</i>

692
00:39:10,966 --> 00:39:12,281
How was it today?

693
00:39:14,002 --> 00:39:16,185
- Bad as you thought it would be?
- Kind of.

694
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:21,307
We need to talk.
We have to, but...

695
00:39:22,093 --> 00:39:24,728
No, you don't. At
least, not tonight.

696
00:39:27,849 --> 00:39:30,249
You weren't even supposed
to be here today. Come on.

697
00:39:31,970 --> 00:39:35,271
<i>You fight and you
fight and you fight.</i>

698
00:39:36,207 --> 00:39:37,490
<i>To what end?</i>

699
00:39:44,582 --> 00:39:45,881
Come home.

700
00:39:47,202 --> 00:39:48,896
<i>What are we fighting against?</i>

701
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:50,869
<i>What are we fighting for?</i>

702
00:39:55,143 --> 00:39:56,992
Just get a good night's sleep.

703
00:40:01,833 --> 00:40:04,353
I never wanted to come
between the two of you.

704
00:40:04,936 --> 00:40:07,704
You and Jackson.
I never wanted that.

705
00:40:09,357 --> 00:40:10,456
I know.

706
00:40:11,075 --> 00:40:14,593
<i>When is it time to just
quit all this nonsense...</i>

707
00:40:32,947 --> 00:40:35,631
Well, good night.

708
00:40:37,852 --> 00:40:39,269
<i>And simply...</i>

709
00:40:40,439 --> 00:40:41,471
<i>surrender.</i>

710
00:40:46,277 --> 00:40:48,939
- That's one nasty throat tumor.
- Oh, God.

711
00:40:48,963 --> 00:40:52,248
- En bloc resection?
- Maybe. Maybe.

712
00:40:53,384 --> 00:40:56,536
Got a patient up at the
Avery hospital in Montana.

713
00:40:57,655 --> 00:41:00,439
I might have to go
out there for a consult.

714
00:41:02,877 --> 00:41:05,189
- Huh.
- "Huh" what?

715
00:41:05,213 --> 00:41:07,174
I'm going to an Avery hospital,

716
00:41:07,198 --> 00:41:09,426
now you're going
to an Avery hospital.

717
00:41:09,450 --> 00:41:12,897
- Oh, come on, really?
- Yeah, it's not that.

718
00:41:12,921 --> 00:41:16,050
Are you... are you
jealous? Is that it?

719
00:41:16,074 --> 00:41:18,435
Jealous of my mom
manipulating you? No.

720
00:41:18,459 --> 00:41:20,192
Oh, stop.

721
00:41:21,162 --> 00:41:22,442
I'm not some puppet.

722
00:41:22,881 --> 00:41:25,665
I have my own brain. I
have my own opinions.

723
00:41:26,017 --> 00:41:27,695
Working with your
mom and the foundation,

724
00:41:27,719 --> 00:41:29,680
it's full of
opportunities for me.

725
00:41:29,704 --> 00:41:32,064
And I get that you never
wanted that, and that's fine.

726
00:41:32,206 --> 00:41:34,941
- But she sees something in me.
- All right, I'm going to bed.

727
00:41:37,311 --> 00:41:38,622
What is going on with you?

728
00:41:38,646 --> 00:41:40,658
Nothing's going on with
me. Just leave it alone.

729
00:41:40,682 --> 00:41:42,832
- Jackson, I...
- It's not your business!

730
00:41:47,855 --> 00:41:48,895
Good night.
